{"id": "EUVD-2022-55254", "enisaUuid": "d4de11b8-17b2-31c5-b435-b1ba2c3e76b9", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nHID: nintendo: fix rumble worker null pointer deref\n\nWe can dereference a null pointer trying to queue work to a destroyed\nworkqueue.\n\nIf the device is disconnected, nintendo_hid_remove is called, in which\nthe rumble_queue is destroyed. Avoid using that queue to defer rumble\nwork once the controller state is set to JOYCON_CTLR_STATE_REMOVED.\n\nThis eliminates the null pointer dereference.", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:39", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-13T21:31:17", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7c6e6c334154be16740b44dcd7638fb510b9bd91", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1ff89e06c2e5fab30274e4b02360d4241d6e605e", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49974"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49974"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "07e7efa9-9795-322d-a68f-25d9846a75ab", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2af16c1f846bd60240745bbd3afa13d5f040c61a <1ff89e06c2e5fab30274e4b02360d4241d6e605e"}, {"id": "1ff86fef-d058-3cd5-a198-3f9584d5d3a2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2af16c1f846bd60240745bbd3afa13d5f040c61a <7c6e6c334154be16740b44dcd7638fb510b9bd91"}, {"id": "35794896-2ce7-39bc-9085-4198a5a0fad2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.16"}, {"id": "80b2eb8f-6157-3f79-bd96-c5236dc17ee2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0"}, {"id": "8fc31049-2a38-31a9-9a07-44b5ed55824e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.7"}, {"id": "cf7b5908-385a-344a-be3e-d89ffe23fe3a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "42d43290-0b3c-309a-b9ac-3aecd892c70c", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}